  "prompt": "Why can't I answer a question twice on Quora?",
  "response": "Quora has implemented a policy to prevent users from answering the same question multiple times in order to maintain the quality and relevance of content on the platform. This rule helps to:\n\n1. Reduce spam and repetitive content: By limiting users to one answer per question, Quora reduces the chances of users posting multiple similar answers, which can be seen as spam.\n\n2. Encourage concise and comprehensive answers: Users are encouraged to provide a single, well-rounded answer that covers all the relevant points, instead of posting multiple fragmented answers.\n\n3. Improve user experience: When users search for information on Quora, they expect to find a variety of perspectives and information in one place. Multiple answers from the same user can clutter the page and make it harder for readers to find diverse viewpoints.\n\nIf you have more information to add or want to update your answer, you can always edit your existing answer to include new details or clarify points. This way, you can provide the most accurate and comprehensive information possible within the limits of Quora's policies.",
